		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>If you don't want to commit to a full bear (or even full feral or hybrid!) build, you can still greatly enhance your tank viability in 5-10man runs by spending a measly 11 points in Feral:<br />
<br />
5/5 Ferocity: The rage cost reduction on Maul is a huge help.<br />
3/5 Feral Instinct: More aggro is good, and more sneakiness is fun.<br />
1/1 Feral Charge: Love this; save 10 rage vs. all knockbacking mobs!<br />
2/? Discretionary. I'd spend them on filling out Feral Instinct, on bash duration, or more crits.<br />
<br />
<br />
For reference, the &quot;cookie cutter&quot; full-bear build is:<br />
<br />
5/5 Ferocity<br />
5/5 Feral Instinct<br />
1/1 Feral Charge<br />
5/5 Thick Hide<br />
3/3 Sharpened Claws<br />
3/3 Predatory Strikes<br />
2/2 Savage Fury<br />
2/2 Primal Fury<br />
1/1 Faerie Fire (Feral)<br />
5/5 Heart of the Wild<br />
1/1 Leader of the Pack<br />
<br />
5/5 Furor<br />
2/2 Improved Enrage<br />
<br />
1/1 Nature's Grasp<br />
4/4 Improved Nature's Grasp<br />
5/5 Natural Weapons<br />
1/1 Omen of Clarity</div>
